http://rogerdudler.github.io/git-guide/index.ko.html

#1. Installing
sudo apt-get install git

#2. Conf
git config --global user.name "user_name"
git config --global user.email "email_id"

#3. Create local repository
Create a folder in my system. This will serve as a local repository which will later be pushed onto the GitHub website.

git init Mytest
cd Mytest

#4. Create a README file (optional)
gedit README

#5. Add repository files to an index
git add README
git add file1
git add folder1
...


#6. Commit changes made to the index
git commit -m "some_message"


#7. Create a repository on GitHub
Name of the repos should be the same as the repos on the local system.

git remote add origin address

#8. Pushing files in local repository to GitHub repository
git push origin master


** 그 외 명령어들
mkdir git-repos
cd git-repos
git clone https://github.com/user_name/~.git

GitHub에 있는 파일을 내 시스템으로 불러옴
